---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'GeoBlue in Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-geoblue', text: 'Why GeoBlue for Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'us-expat-benefits', text: 'US Expat Benefits', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Panama', href: '/countries/panama/insurance' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue Review', href: '/providers/geoblue' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue vs Cigna', href: '/compare/geoblue-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 55)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Xplorer Essential', coverage: 'Core coverage', price: '$230-300/mo' },
  { plan: 'Xplorer Select', coverage: 'Enhanced', price: '$300-400/mo' },
  { plan: 'Xplorer Premier', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$380-480/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="GeoBlue Health Insurance in Panama"
  description="Guide to GeoBlue international health insurance for US expats in Panama. BCBS network access and seamless US-Panama coverage."
  headline="GeoBlue in Panama"
  subheadline="BCBS-affiliated international coverage. Ideal for US expats maintaining strong connections to American healthcare."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/panama-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a GeoBlue Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/geoblue"
>
  <h2 id="overview">GeoBlue in Panama</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue is the international health insurance arm of the Blue Cross Blue Shield Association. For American expats in Panama, GeoBlue offers seamless coverage between both countries with access to the extensive BCBS network in the US.
  </p>
  <p>
    Given Panama's large American retiree population, GeoBlue's US-focused approach resonates with those who want to maintain healthcare connections to home.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$280-450</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 55)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">BCBS</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Network access</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">US Focus</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">American expats</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your GeoBlue Panama Quote"
    description="BCBS-backed coverage for US expats."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-geoblue">Why GeoBlue for Panama</h2>

  <h3>BCBS Network Access</h3>
  <p>
    When you return to the US, you have access to the Blue Cross Blue Shield network—one of the largest in America:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Over 1.7 million healthcare professionals</li>
    <li>90% of hospitals in the US</li>
    <li>Negotiated rates for US care</li>
    <li>No need for separate US travel insurance</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Designed for Americans Abroad</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue specifically serves Americans living overseas:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>US-based customer service</li>
    <li>Claims processes designed for American expectations</li>
    <li>Compliance with US regulations</li>
    <li>Integration with US healthcare systems</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Panama Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue covers care at Panama's quality private hospitals:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Hospital Punta Pacífica</li>
    <li>Hospital Nacional</li>
    <li>Centro Médico Paitilla</li>
    <li>English-speaking assistance</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Perfect for Snowbirds</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      If you split time between Panama and the US, GeoBlue's seamless coverage in both countries eliminates the hassle of managing multiple policies or worrying about coverage gaps.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 55-year-old. Premiums vary based on age, health, and selected coverage options.
  </p>

  <h3>Plan Levels</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Xplorer Essential:</strong> Inpatient, emergency, evacuation—core protection</li>
    <li><strong>Xplorer Select:</strong> Adds outpatient, specialists, expanded benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Xplorer Premier:</strong> Comprehensive coverage with enhanced limits and wellness</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Deductible Options</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue offers various deductibles to manage costs:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>$0 - Full first-dollar coverage</li>
    <li>$1,000-$2,500 - Moderate premium reduction</li>
    <li>$5,000+ - Significant savings for catastrophic focus</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, intensive care</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, diagnostics (Select+)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency care</li>
    <li><strong>Prescriptions:</strong> Prescription drug coverage included</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation and repatriation</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Coverage available in higher tiers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>GeoBlue-Specific Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Destination physician profiles (research doctors before visits)</li>
    <li>Mobile app with doctor and hospital finder</li>
    <li>Translate health documents</li>
    <li>24/7 multilingual support</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: Medical underwriting required</li>
    <li>Age limits: Generally up to age 84 for new enrollment</li>
    <li>US-citizen focused: May not be available to non-Americans</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="us-expat-benefits">US Expat Benefits</h2>

  <h3>Medicare Gap Solution</h3>
  <p>
    US Medicare doesn't cover care abroad. For American retirees in Panama:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>GeoBlue provides primary coverage in Panama</li>
    <li>BCBS network access when visiting US</li>
    <li>Some coordination possible if you maintain Medicare</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Family Visits</h3>
  <p>
    When visiting family in the US:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Full coverage at BCBS network providers</li>
    <li>No need for separate travel insurance</li>
    <li>Seamless claims processing</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Medical Return Option</h3>
  <p>
    For complex medical situations, returning to the US is an option:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to US specialists and hospitals</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation coverage</li>
    <li>Coordination of care between countries</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Age-Related Pricing</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age 55:</strong> $280-450/month</li>
    <li><strong>Age 65:</strong> $400-650/month</li>
    <li><strong>Age 75:</strong> $550-850/month</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare GeoBlue Plans for Panama"
    description="BCBS-backed coverage for American expats."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> GeoBlue is designed for US citizens and may not be available to all nationalities. Prices are estimates—get a personalized quote for accurate pricing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
